  "steps": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Press pie crust into a 9-inch pie dish and crimp the edges.",
    "Whisk together all filling ingredients until smooth. Pour into the unbaked crust.",
    "Make the streusel: combine flour, sugar, and chopped nuts, then cut in the cold butter with a fork or your fingers until it resembles coarse crumbles.",
    "Sprinkle the streusel evenly over the filling.",
    "Bake for 45–55 minutes until the filling is set — it should be mostly firm with just a slight jiggle in the centre. If the crust edges are browning too fast, cover them with foil.",
    "Cool completely on a rack before slicing. Refrigerate leftovers."
